cords, and women’s own raw, caustic , and darkly funny narratives, Wayward Women provides a riveting portrait of the way modernity engages with gender to produce new and contested subjectivities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aBride pricexPapua New GuineaxTari District. 0aBride pricezPapua New GuineazTari District. 0aCourtshipxPapua New GuineaxTari District. 0aCourtshipzPapua New GuineazTari District. 0aWomen, HulixEconomic conditionsxPapua New GuineaxTari District. 0aWomen, HulixSexual behaviorxPapua New GuineaxTari District. 0aWomen, HulixSexual behaviorzPapua New GuineazTari District. 0aWomen, HulixSocial conditionsxPapua New GuineaxTari District. 0aWomen, HulizPapua New GuineazTari DistrictxEconomic conditions. 0aWomen, HulizPapua New GuineazTari DistrictxSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aanthropologists.  abridewealth.  acapitalist economy.  acontemporary papua new guinea.  acourt cases.  aethnography.  afemale agency.  agender issues.  agender studies.  agendered violence.  ahuli women.  amarriage.  amodern world.  anew guinea society.  anonfiction.  apapua new guinea.  apassenger women.  apersonal experiences.  aprostitution.  arape.  asex workers.  asexuality.  asocial institutions.  asocioeconomic factors.  atransactional sex.  avillage law.  awomen and families.  awomen.  awomens roles.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093897740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520938977423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520938977/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000